<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="348" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,325,496]" pageId="47" pageNumber="348">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,398,424]" pageId="47" pageNumber="348">Remarks.</emphasis>
We refigure one of the two cranidia figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Reed, F. R. C." box="[841,983,398,424]" pageId="47" pageNumber="348" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref46843" refString="Reed, F. R. C. (1917) Ordovician and Silurian fossils from Yun-nan. Palaeontologia Indica, 6 (3), 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1917">Reed (1917)</bibRefCitation>
. He figured a detail of an external mould showing strong terrace ridges on the front of the cephalic shield, and this feature is suggested also on the internal surface. There are few other features, and a critical determination is impossible without further material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
